com.google.enterprise.connector.util.filter
Class ModifyPropertyFilter

java.lang.Object
  com.google.enterprise.connector.util.filter.AbstractDocumentFilter
      com.google.enterprise.connector.util.filter.ModifyPropertyFilter
All Implemented Interfaces:
DocumentFilterFactory
public class ModifyPropertyFilter
extends AbstractDocumentFilter

A Document filter that alters the values of the specified Properties. The filter will scrutinize the Values returned by the supplied Properties. If the value (as a string) matches the regular expression pattern, then all matching regions of the value will be replace with the replacement string. The modified value may then either augment or overwrite the original value.

setReplacement

public void setReplacement(java.lang.String replacement)
Sets the replacement string for matching regions in the values. The replacement string may refer to capturing groups from the pattern as $1, $2, etc. Therefore, literal instances of '\' and '$' in the replacement string need to be properly escaped.

Parameters:
replacement - the replacement String for matching regions in the values

setOverwrite

public void setOverwrite(boolean overwrite)
Sets the overwrite values flag. If true, matching values are overwritten with the modified value. If false, matching values are augmented by adding an additional modified value. Default overwrite is false.

Parameters:
overwrite - the overwrite flag

findProperty

public Property findProperty(Document source,
                             java.lang.String name)
                      throws RepositoryException
Finds a Property by name. If the source Document has a property of that name, then that property is returned.

Values returned by the supplied Properties. If any of the Property's values (as a string) match the regular expression pattern, then all matching regions of the value will be replace with the replacement string.

The modified value may either augment or overwrite the original value, based upon the overwrite flag.
